  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN131.1-kilavi">poruḷkaṭaikkūṭṭiya neñciṟkut talaimakaṉ colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What HE said to [his] heart that was coveting wealth.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN131.1">
                <l>vicumpuṟa nivanta māttā ḷitaṇaip</l>
                <l>pacuṅkēḻ mellilai yarukuneṟit taṉṉa</l>
                <l>vaṇṭupaṭu piruḷiya tāḻiruṅ kūntaṟ</l>
                <l>curumpuṇa virinta peruntaṇ kōtai</l>
                <l>yivaḷiṉuñ ciṟantaṉ <supplied>ṟī</supplied>ta ṉamakkeṉa</l>
                <l>vīḷai yampiṉ viḻuttoṭai maḻavar</l>
                <l>nāḷā <supplied>vu</supplied>ytta nāmaveñ curattu</l>
                <l>naṭaimelin toḻinta cēṭpaṭar kaṉṟiṉ</l>
                <l>kaṭaimaṇi yukunīr tuṭaitta vāṭavar</l>
                <l>peyarum pīṭu meḻuti yatartoṟum</l>
                <l>pīli cūṭṭiya piṟaṅkunilai naṭukal</l>
                <l>vē<supplied>lū</supplied>ṉṟu palakai vē<del>lē</del>ṟṟumuṉai paṭukkum</l>
                <l>veruvaru taku<supplied>na</supplied> kāṉa nammoṭu</l>
                <l>varuku veṉṉuti yāyiṉ</l>
                <l>vārē <supplied>ṉe</supplied>ñcam vāykkani<supplied>ṉ</supplied> viṉaiyē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Saying “giving is more important to us than the one (5)</l>
                <l>with a big cool garland that unfolded so that bees eat [nectar from it],</l>
                <l>on [her] hanging dark tresses that become dark as bees descend [on it], (3f.)</l>
                <l>as if soft leaves with green lustre were curled closely</l>
                <l>around the platform with big stilts that have come up so as to reach the sky”, (1f.)</l>
                <l>if you were to say “let me come with us!” (14)</l>
                <l>to the forest that is fit to frighten [anyone], (13)</l>
                <l>where warriors, with excellent aim in [their] whistling arrows,</l>
                <l>set up another front with shields on which spears lean</l>
                <l>by the memorial stones with glistening bases adorned with peacock feathers</l>
                <l>on every road, inscribing the name and fame of</l>
                <l>men who wiped the water that was shed from the rims of the eye-balls</l>
                <l>of calves setting out into the distance, that stayed behind as [their] gait became weak</l>
                <l>in the fearsome hot desert into which the cows were sent in the morning, (6-11)</l>
                <l>I wouldn’t come, heart. May your work be successful. (15)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
